Subject: Wkermit problems and sugestions

The Wkermit command scanner has some problems.  If a typo is made in
the first word of a command, multiple error messages are displayed.
(i.e. "sat baud 9600" will show 3 unrecognised command errors.)  "?"
will only display after a return, and will place the cursor at the
begining rather than the end of the command in question.  I also
dislike the wkermit startup banner.

The default window size is two large for our configuration.  (9600
baud port selector connection.)  It's to bad the prime can't check
the input buffer size and advertise an appropriate size window.

Bob Larson <Blarson@Usc-Ecl.Arpa>

